        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>37 Beresford Road<lb/>
                Highbury New Park<lb/>
                Islington. N.<lb/>
                London 27 July&#47;70<lb/>
                Revd. S Morais<lb/>
                My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your favor of 12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Inst. afforded me<lb/> the pleasing opportunity of serving you&#44;<lb/> and I beg to assure you that I shall always<lb/> be most happy to attend to any affair interesting<lb/> to you&#44; within my limited power.<lb/></p>
            <p>Enclosed I send the Note &#38; answer<lb/> from my relative who is secretary of the Instn.<lb/> I regret that it is not more favorable.<lb/></p>
            <p>Mrs. N &#38; sisters unite with me<lb/> in the pleasure derived from knowing that<lb/> your family circle is complete and well&#58;<lb/> your mother&#39;s in law&#39;s removal from time<lb/> to eternity can scarcely&#44; as you justly observed&#44;<lb/> be looked on as a loss&#44; considering her age &#38; infirmity<lb/> We all thank you for your kind expressions of<lb/> condolence&#44; and send our sincere regards<lb/> to your dear wife children &#38; yourself<lb/></p>
            <p>ever yours truly<lb/>
                &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr &#38; Mrs Almosnino are just now at Margate<lb/> the latter has been a cripple for some months&#44; the<lb/> right leg is almost paralyzed&#44; I fear it will not be better<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Rev S Morais<lb/>
                546 North 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Street<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                United States<lb/></p>

        </body>
